  "dct:title": "NOMAD plugin system",
  "dct:description": "This page introduces the NOMAD plugin system, which enables modular, customizable extensions to the NOMAD platform without modifying its core. It outlines how plugins are structured and integrated using distributions, entry points, and Python packaging. By leveraging entry points, users and developers can add new features such as parsers, schema packages, apps, and APIs. The page explains the architecture, configuration, lazy-loading mechanism, and discovery process of plugins, making it easier to adapt NOMAD to diverse research needs. It also provides guidance for writing, configuring, and loading plugins effectively.",
